man Gossett}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[South Carolina Circuit Court|South Carolina Circuit Solicitor for the 7th district]]|years=2001\u20132011}}\n{{s-aft|after=Barry Barnette}}\n|-\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{USRepSuccessionBox\n| state=South Carolina\n| district=4 \n| before=[[Bob Inglis]] \n| start=2011\n}}\n|-\n{{s-new|office}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Chair of the [[United States House Select Committee on Benghazi|House Benghazi Committee]]|years=2014\u20132016}}\n{{s-non|reason=Position abolished}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Jason Chaffetz]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Chair of the [[United States House Committee on Oversight and Government Reform|House Oversight Committee]]|years=2017\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|usa}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Paul Gosar]]<br>R-[[Arizona]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Seniority in the United States House of Representatives|United States Representatives by seniority]]|years=207th}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Morgan Griffith]]<br>R-[[Virginia]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{SC-FedRep}}\n{{USHouseCurrent}}\n{{USHouseChairs}}\n{{US House Oversight and Government Reform chairs}}\n{{USCongRep-start|congresses=112th\u2013115th [[United States Congress]]es |state=[[South Carolina]]}}\n{{USCongRep/SC/112}}\n{{USCongRep/SC/113}}\n{{USCongRep/SC/114}}\n{{USCongRep/SC/115}}\n{{USCongRep-end}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gowdy, Trey}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:Assistant United States Attorneys]]\n[[Category:Baylor University alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the United States House of Representatives from South Carolina]]\n[[Category:Tea Party movement activists]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Spartanburg, South Carolina]]\n[[Category:Republican Party members of the United States House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:South Carolina lawyers]]\n[[Category:South Carolina Republicans]]\n[[Category:South Carolina state solicitors]]\n[[Category:Southern Baptists]]\n[[Category:University of South Carolina School of